Bootstrap the Data Frames in a List

Source: R/bootstrap_list.R
bootstrap_list.Rd

This function takes a data frame and returns a list of data frames that are bootstrapped from the original data frame.

Usage

bootstrap_list(x, n = 1000, rows = 1000, seed = NULL, dfidx = FALSE, ...)

Arguments

x

The original data frame.

n

The number of bootstrapped data frames to return.

rows

The number of rows to sample from the original data frame.

seed

The seed to use for the random number generator. Default is NULL.

dfidx

If TRUE, use the dfidx::dfidx function to transform into mlogit data format, i.e., a dataframe with indexes. Default is FALSE.

...

Additional arguments to pass to dfidx::dfidx.

Value

A list of data frames.

Examples

df <- data.frame(no = seq(length(state.abb)), stabb = state.abb)
bootstrap_list(df)
